definition:
affording light mirth and laughter : amusing                                      
             
             His account of the war came in bits and pieces, sometimes bloody, sometimes funny.

seeking or intended to amuse : facetious                                      
             
             Don't take him so seriously; he was just being funny.

differing from the ordinary in a suspicious, perplexing, quaint, or eccentric way : peculiar                                      
             
             My car has been making a funny noise.

involving trickery or deception                                      
             
             told his prisoner not to try anything funny
one that is funny

comic strips or the comic section of a periodical                                      
                
                  —usually used with the
causing laughter
odd or strange
not well : somewhat ill

causing laughter : full of humor                                      
             
             a funny story

strange sense 2                                      
             
             a funny noise

in an odd or peculiar way                                      
             
             She looked at me funny.
